OL,3,C800 mothers share 'traumatic'
OL,4,Cexperience on Homerton ward
OL,6,FThe former patient said: "Time and
OL,7,Ftime again the feedback was coming
OL,8,Fback about the post natal ward that it
OL,9,Fwas a dire situation and it looked
OL,10,Flike over time it was just getting
OL,11,Fworse and worse and worse.
OL,13,F"The hospital were aware of it. My
OL,14,Foutgoing chair had raised it with them
OL,15,Fmany times.
OL,17,F"The temperature levels in the summer
OL,18,Fget to some crazy numbers and women
OL,19,Fare fainting, midwives are fainting
OL,20,Fand nothing was being done about it."
