OL,3,C800 mothers share 'traumatic'
OL,4,Cexperience on Homerton ward
OL,6,FFormer patient Anna Clarkson, said:
OL,7,F"It felt like I was on a Nightingale
OL,8,Fward in a World War one film. So many
OL,9,Fof us cramped in, tiny cubicles and it
OL,10,Fwas sweltering.
OL,12,F"My husband jokingly asked if I was
OL,13,Fmelting - I was dripping with sweat.
OL,15,F"This shouldn't be the way we treat
OL,16,Fpeople at the most vulnerable moment
OL,17,Fof their lives. We're talking about
OL,18,Fthe future health of parents and
OL,19,Fchildren and it always feels it's at
OL,20,Fthe bottom of the pile."
